  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition : 1 - Text to be entered\r\nReason:\r\n",
    "Condition : 2 - Text to be entered\r\nReason:\r\n",
    "Condition : 3 - Text to be entered\r\nReason:\r\n",
    "Reason : 1 - The proposed development includes the retention of a 11sqm commercial unit which given its very small size would not be attractive to a range of occupiers contrary to the provisions of policy DMS1 paragraph k of the Councils adopted Development Management Policies Document (DMPD) (adopted 2016).  ",
    "Reason : 2 - \r\nThe proposal would result in a sub-standard level of residential accommodation given the undersized nature of all of the dwellings and the very poor level of outlook and daylight penetration that would be afforded to the rear of the ground floor dwelling, contrary to the provisions the emerging Local Plan, the London Plan, the national space standards and polices DMH4 and DMH6 of the Councils adopted Development Management Policies Document (DMPD) (adopted 2016).  \r\n",
    "Reason : 3 - The site is located within flood risk zone 2 and ground floor bedrooms are proposed, however the submitted Flood Risk Assessment does not adequately confirm that it is safe for bedrooms to be provided at this level, contrary to the provisions of policy DMS5 of the Councils adopted Development Management Policies Document (DMPD) (adopted 2016).  ",
    "Reason : 4 - You are encouraged to consider submission of a fresh application incorporating the material amendments set out below which are necessary to make the scheme acceptable. \r\n\r\nRequired amendments:\r\n- Provide a larger commercial unit of at least 45sqm;\r\n- Demonstrate that the dwellings are 1-person units and significantly change the layout of the proposed ground floor dwelling;\r\n- Adequately demonstrate that the finished floor levels would provide safe accommodation in flood risk terms.  \r\n\r\n"
  ],
